1681<div>

1682<h3>

1683<strong>

1684What Types of Lighting are There?</strong>

1685&nbsp;</h3>

1686

1687

1688<p>

1689There are three types of lighting: general lighting (also known as ambient), accent lighting, and task lighting. A room may have one or a combination of the following:&nbsp;</p>

1690

1691

1692<p>

1693<strong>

1694General lighting</strong>

1695 is the main light in the room. This includes natural light from windows, ceiling lights, or recessed lighting.&nbsp;</p>

1696

1697

1698<p>

1699<strong>

1700Accent lighting</strong>

1701 illuminates an area or element in a room, like a reading area, kitchen island, or reading nook. Use lamps, pendant lighting, chandeliers, or sconces to achieve the right look.&nbsp;</p>

1702

1703

1704<p>

1705<strong>

1706Task lighting</strong>

1707 is a fixture that adds extra light to perform a task. Picture a light over the sink for washing dishes, under cabinet lights to prepare food, or a reading lamp next to the bed.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>

1708

1709

1710<p>

1711With that in mind, browse our collection of ceiling lights to brighten up your home.&nbsp;</p>

1712

1713

1714<p>

1715&nbsp;</p>

1716

1717</div>

1718</div>
